issue.title: [Feature Request] Allow IDEs to support IntelliSense on virtual components
issue.body:
### Problem to solve
VSCode and Webstorm currently have no way to knowing when a user creates a virtual component in Vuetify. See https://vuetifyjs.com/en/features/aliasing and https://discord.com/channels/340160225338195969/1166761642026086420 for details.

Adding support for this will greatly improve the DX and accessibility of the virtual component feature.

### Proposed solution
I'm not really sure what the solution here should be aside from creating some kind of code generator that will work with volar or typescript that would let it know about the existence of the components. I did some research into what the [anu project](https://github.com/jd-solanki/anu) is doing and I don't think their implementation is any better at figuring this out... I tried it its only a little bit different from what Vuetify does for component registrations.

issue.title: [Feature Request] Export TS types, interfaces

labels.name: framework
labels.description: Issues and Feature Requests that have needs framework-wide.

issue.body:
### Problem to solve
Let's consider next struct
```
const headers: DataTableHeader[] = [
  { title: '#', key: 'id' },
  { title: t('messages.name'), key: 'name' },
  { title: t('messages.lat'), key: 'lat' },
  { title: t('messages.lng'), key: 'lng' },
  { title: t('messages.state'), key: 'state', value: 'state.name', sortable: false },
  { title: t('messages.country'), key: 'country', value: 'state.country.name', sortable: false },
]
if(can('upsert', 'city')) {
  headers.push({ title: t('messages.actions'), key: 'action', sortable: false, align: 'end' })
}
```

We as developers don't have access to defined types, interfaces as a result in my project I have to duplicate the same TS types

### Proposed solution
Just add export to types, interfaces that you already defined

issue.title: [Bug Report][3.3.22] v-combobox clears all values when a duplicate value is entered
issue.body:
### Environment
**Vuetify Version:** 3.3.22
**Last working version:** 2.6.12
**Vue Version:** 3.3.4
**Browsers:** Chrome 118.0.0.0
**OS:** Mac OS 10.15.7

### Steps to reproduce
You can actually reproduce this using the example on the combobox docs page.

1. Enable "multiple" prop
- can enable "chips" but it will behave the same either way
2. Type in an option and hit enter- if using the example on the docs page type in "Colorado" and hit enter
Result: the item is selected
3. Type in the same option and hit enter again -- for example, type in "Colorado" and hit enter
Result: The term (ex: Colorado) is cleared from the selection entirely

### Expected Behavior
The search term should remain selected but no duplicate values should be listed.

### Actual Behavior
The duplicated search term is entirely removed.

### Reproduction Link
[https://play.vuetifyjs.com/#...](https://play.vuetifyjs.com/#eNpNkMsKgzAQRX8lzMaNVdCuxApFaH+g0IW6iJraQMyE+MBS+u/VqMTV3DnzYO5kX+h05V+V8saBQQRxz1olaM+SXBISjyeqlJEmqVD2lEumN7TBtsQSpx0RUr256mzaDqLnSjBLBC2ZuOSQ7qNgaxGfT+jmYuakVPAXasmp4xInRYGa1rjo2yx5bfCdoW7WjgebaLeI5wdbLhunsIuT2Len7o4MOlpayOo49g+fgJ8LoRd6Z1hjEEDxB4UUXvg=)

issue.title: [Bug Report][3.3.23] Nested routes breaks theme-related styling
issue.body:
### Environment
**Vuetify Version:** 3.3.23
**Vue Version:** 3.3.7
**Browsers:** Chrome 118.0.0.0
**OS:** Mac OS 10.15.7

### Steps to reproduce
1) Install and start the development server (see README) or open the Stackblitz provided.
2) Visit "Index" and refresh the page (works as expected)
3) Visit "Issue" and refresh the page (theme styling breaks)
4) Visit "Nested issue" and refresh the page (theme styling breaks)
5) Visit "grandchild" and refresh the page (works as expected)

When visiting "grandchild" after the theme is broken it also applies the styles correctly.

### Expected Behavior
The theme styles should be loaded correctly for all routes.

### Actual Behavior
The theme styles does not load correctly when you load a page/route that has children.

### Reproduction Link
[https://github.com/mathiasrando/nuxt3-vuetify-issue-nested-routes](https://github.com/mathiasrando/nuxt3-vuetify-issue-nested-routes)

### Other comments
If you go to "nested-issue.vue" and removes "<NuxtPage></NuxtPage>" so that the child route cannot load reloading "Nested issue" no longer breaks the styling.

Here is also a Stackblitz link with the minimal reproduction: https://stackblitz.com/edit/nuxt-starter-6q9lur?file=README.md

issue.title: [Bug Report][3.3.22] v-model not updating on VDatePicker
issue.body:
### Environment
**Vuetify Version:** 3.3.22
**Vue Version:** 3.3.6
**Browsers:** Chrome 118.0.0.0
**OS:** Mac OS 10.15.7

### Steps to reproduce
Create a VDatePicker. Pass it a v-model ref. Ref does not update. It doesn't work with the listener either ('$emit(@update:modelValue')). The event seems to be emitted from VDatePickerMonth but does not seem to be propagated to VDatePicker.

### Expected Behavior
Expect event to be emitted from VDatePicker

### Actual Behavior
Event is not emitted from VDatePicker

issue.title: [Bug Report][3.4.0-alpha.1] v-otp-input enters focus infinite loop when typing really fast
issue.body:
### Environment
**Vuetify Version:** 3.4.0-alpha.1
**Vue Version:** 3.3.7
**Browsers:** Chrome 117.0.0.0
**OS:** Mac OS 10.15.7

### Steps to reproduce
1. Follow [contribute guide](https://vuetifyjs.com/en/getting-started/contributing/#vuetify) and run vuetify dev mode
2. Load playground code to Playground.vue
3. Open `packages/vuetify/src/labs/VOtpInput/VOtpInput.tsx`
4. Put `console.log('onFocus', index)` in line 175
5. Put `console.log('onBlur')` in line 182
6. Run `yarn dev` from project root
7. Type some numbers really fast

### Expected Behavior
It should behave the same as typing slowly

### Actual Behavior
As per console log in chrome dev tool, `onFocus` and `onBlur` are triggered in infinite loop


https://github.com/vuetifyjs/vuetify/assets/5698884/99724df5-dbe9-4df6-bf55-63c848a76b7b



### Reproduction Link
[https://play.vuetifyjs.com/#...](https://play.vuetifyjs.com/#)
